elements.title: his sons' architecture firm
elements.contents: ... that I. M. Pei said that his sons' architecture firm "came of age" while designing the Bank of China head office (pictured) in Beijing?

elements.title: capturing Malacca in 1641
elements.contents: ... that despite losing almost one thousand men capturing Malacca in 1641, the Dutch East India Company did not invest much time or energy into it afterward?

elements.title: Marilyn Gayle Hoff

elements.title: Bern Disputation

elements.title: John Custis

elements.title: Milton Loch
elements.contents: ... that the crannogs of Milton Loch, although similar in design, span a time period of around 1,000 years?

elements.title: John Hart Ely
elements.contents: ... that American legal scholar John Hart Ely penned a law review article castigating the Supreme Court's decision in Roe v. Wade, despite being pro-choice?

elements.title: Boom Town
elements.contents: ... that Sonia Levitin was inspired to write Boom Town after reading about a California girl who baked $11,000 worth of pies during the Gold Rush?
